      "source": [
        "### Issue #2: Dispersed Dog Breed Information"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "collapsed": true,
        "extensions": {
          "jupyter_dashboards": {
            "version": 1,
            "views": {
              "grid_default": {
                "hidden": true
              },
              "report_default": {
                "hidden": true
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "id": "rEN-OI3bt6uv"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### Define: The `doggo`, `floofer`, `pupper`, and `puppo` columns, which represent different dog stages or types, contain sparse information. These columns will be combined into a single `dog_breed` column to consolidate dog breed information."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "peMqF5j1t-9C"
      },
      "source": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 77,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c4j0PnJiuBkb"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Combining the 'doggo', 'floofer', 'pupper', and 'puppo' columns into a new column 'dog_breed'\n",
        "# The .combine_first() method is used to fill missing values from the first column with non-missing values from the next columns\n",
        "twitter_archive['dog_breed'] = twitter_archive['doggo']\\\n",
        "                                  .combine_first(twitter_archive['floofer'])\\\n",
        "                                  .combine_first(twitter_archive['pupper'])\\\n",
        "                                  .combine_first(twitter_archive['puppo'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Dropping the original 'doggo', 'floofer', 'pupper', and 'puppo' columns from the twitter_archive DataFrame as they are no longer needed\n",
        "twitter_archive = twitter_archive.drop(columns=['doggo', 'floofer', 'pupper', 'puppo'])"
      ]
    },
